Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Thinly slice @Dill Pickle{1} into rounds.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{4%teaspoon}, half the @Fry Seasoning{1%tablespoon} (you'll use the rest later), @Salt{}, and @Pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and crispy, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Creamy Mustard Sauce ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @Dijon Mustard{2%teaspoon}, and @Sugar{1/2%teaspoon} (1 tsp for 4 servings). Season with salt and pepper.

== Pork Patties ==

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @Ground Pork{10%ounce}, @Cumin{1%teaspoon}, and remaining Fry Seasoning. Season generously with salt (we used ¾ tsp; use 1 1/2 tsp for 4 servings) and pepper. Form into two equal-sized patties (four patties for 4), each a bit wider than a burger bun.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add patties and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side. One minute before they're done, top each patty with @Monterey Jack Cheese{1/4%cup}; cover to melt cheese and allow patties to finish cooking.

== Assembly ==

Halve @Potato Buns{2}. Place @Butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}. Microwave until melted, about ~{30%seconds}. Toast buns until golden brown, then brush with melted butter. Fill each with a patty, pickle slices, and sauce. Serve with potato wedges on the side.

> This burger takes inspiration from the Cubano—a beloved, porky sandwich. Our burger-fied rendition boasts toasty, buttered buns, juicy pork patties, melty mozz, crunchy pickles, and a creamy dijon sauce. Plus a side of fries—because how could we not?